fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "This book talks about the delicate..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This book talks about the delicate nature of 'toos, as well as introducing some of the most popular species among the bird enthusiasts: the funeral cockatoo, the Major Majestic cockatoo, and the most common bang-bang cockatoo. It's colourfully illustrated.

From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "Pet owners also report moodiness, l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pet owners also report moodiness, loudness and hostility as reoccurring issues. If left unsatisfied cockatoos may scream non-stop, pluck their feathers or become aggressive.

fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "A cockatoo is a parrot with an erec..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cockatoo is a parrot with an erectile crest, found on the Semenine islands and in southern Face-Ã -la-Mer. Known for their intelligence and general precociousness, cockatoos are popular birds in aviculture; however, they often exhibit various behavioural issues.

fields.Title: You: "Yes, but there has to be something..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, but there has to be something *great* about cockatoos as well.

fields.Title: You: "The grey and common bang-bang, that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The grey and common bang-bang, that's me.

fields.Title: You: "Isn't that obvious?! Major Majestic..."

From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "Perhaps the most *impressive* of al..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Perhaps the most *impressive* of all the species, the endangered Major Majestic cockatoo is often described as the most flamboyant bird in the jungle, its pink-coloured wings and flowing crest embellishing its proud and *bumptious* nature.

fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "Despite its *banging* name, the ban..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Despite its *banging* name, the bang-bang cockatoo is actually the shyest of the species. Common in almost all Semenese forests, as well as zoos and homes all over the world, its plumage is mainly grey and white. The Semenese name *bang-bang* is thought to be of onomatopoeic origins.

fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "It is not recommended to get a cock..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is not recommended to get a cockatoo if you're not able to cook them food every day. And give them the full care that they need. These birds will never understand that you have a life of your own.

fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "Understandable. Choosing your heral..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Understandable. Choosing your heraldic bird isn't a trivial question.

fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "You're right, you're *Psittacus fun..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're right, you're *Psittacus funereus* embodied. This ominous bird belongs on your heraldry!

fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "You're right, you're the mediocrity..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're right, you're the mediocrity embodied. This unsung bird belongs on your heraldry!

fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "This is a yellow-tailed black cocka..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is a yellow-tailed black cockatoo. Its specific name *Psittacus funereus* relates to its dark and sombre plumage. This bird looks as if dressed for a funeral, 24/7. There is something indisputably ominous about it.

fields.Dialogue Text: Alright, what problems do these birds have?

fields.Title: From A to Zrieek! A Guide To a Well-Behaved Cockatoo: "Where to even begin? All cockatoos..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Where to even begin? All cockatoos are known for their needy natures, requiring attention for at least two full hours a day. They love to talk, and have been described as 'loveable clowns who just don't know how to wrap up'.

fields.Dialogue Text: Only the funeral cockatoo in its darkness can truly grasp the depths of my doom-laden soul.

fields.Dialogue Text: You're right, you're a fuckatoo embodied. This sorry-ass bird belongs on your heraldry! It probably doesn't even have feathers and only screams.
